---
/**
 * rest-api · 0006-pagination-at-scale · Figure 2 — "SAME PAGE SIZE, WILDLY
 * DIFFERENT COST" (OFFSET 0 reads 50 vs OFFSET 1,000,000 reads a million).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/rest-api/lessons/0006-pagination-at-scale.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). Component, not inline, because MDX's JSX parser
 * mishandles kebab-case SVG attributes. This figure uses no arrow markers — the
 * "→" between the two boxes is a plain <text> glyph — so it needs no <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 620 150"
        role="img"
        aria-label="OFFSET 0 reads 50 rows; OFFSET 1,000,000 must read a million rows to hand you fifty"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="310"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">SAME PAGE SIZE, WILDLY DIFFERENT COST</text
            >
            <rect x="20" y="40" width="270" height="86" rx="9" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="155"
                y="60"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">OFFSET 0 LIMIT 50</text
            >
            <rect x="40" y="74" width="60" height="20" rx="3" fill="#fbfaf2" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text x="155" y="89" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#244a2e"
                >reads 50 → returns 50</text
            >
            <text x="155" y="112" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#244a2e"
                >fast · page 1 always looks fine</text
            >
            <rect x="330" y="40" width="270" height="86" rx="9" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="465"
                y="60"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">OFFSET 1,000,000 LIMIT 50</text
            >
            <rect x="350" y="74" width="230" height="20" rx="3" fill="#fbfaf2" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text x="465" y="89" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#7a2218"
                >reads 1,000,050 → returns 50</text
            >
            <text x="465" y="112" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#7a2218"
                >crawls · a million rows thrown away</text
            >
            <text x="310" y="143" text-anchor="middle" font-size="22" fill="#9a2417">→</text>
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        <code>OFFSET 1000000</code> reads a million rows to hand you fifty — the work is in the rows you
        <em>skip</em>, not the rows you keep.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
